Here are some notes on The Bash Cookbook, arranged by Recipe.
It's a Chex-mix of typo corrections, and suggestions, and comments.
Typically, my stuff is indented, while the original is left-justified.
Simple corrections are written like this

old ->
  new

or

old
  -> new

Section "20" (20.1, 20.2, ...) is "Tips and Traps for Jeff" -- they're common
goofs of mine, even though I'm not a novice.
